Package: mvher
Type: Package
Title: Missing Value Handling for Entity Resolution
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-03-01
Authors@R: person("Xinmin", "Chu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "Xinmin.Chu001@umb.edu",
                  comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-5140-3852"))
Description: A comprehensive toolkit for handling missing values (NA and empty
    strings) in entity resolution (ER) and record linkage pipelines.
    Implements eight field-comparison strategies (neutral, zero, Fellegi-Sunter
    gamma-level encoding, indicator augmentation, complete-case, asymmetric, and
    the semantically-flawed 'both-empty=1' default), seven feature-matrix
    imputation strategies (mean, median, zero, half, hot-deck, k-NN, none),
    plus diagnostic utilities for assessing field-level and entity-level
    missingness patterns and recommending the most suitable strategy based on
    data characteristics.
